channel.title: 3 Errors adding vote shop
channel.description:
This is awkward...4th topic in a row made by me.. But oh well, i need help. :l This time i'm 100% sure i can't fix these problems..
Tried to make a vote system by [url=http://www.rune-server.org/runescape-development/google/tutorials/424413-pi-my-vote-system-teaching.html]This[/url] guide, And i got these errors:
[code]src\server\model\players\DialogueHandler.java:25: error: method sendNpcChat4 in class DialogueHandler cannot be applied to given types; sendNpcChat4("Hello, I am the vote master. I handle", "t he collection of vote cash and", "vote points. I can also open the vote", "page. What can I do for you?", c.talkingNpc, "Vote Master"); ^ required: String,String,String,String,int,String,int found: String,String,String,String,int,String reason: actual and formal argument lists differ in length src\server\model\players\DialogueHandler.java:34: error: method sendNpcChat4 in class DialogueHandler cannot be applied to given types; sendNpcChat4("Here is your vote point and cash.", "Remem ber, you can vote every day.", "Voting helps the server grow!", "See you tomorro w!", c.talkingNpc, "Vote Master"); ^ required: String,String,String,String,int,String,int found: String,String,String,String,int,String reason: actual and formal argument lists differ in length src\server\model\players\DialogueHandler.java:40: error: method sendNpcChat4 in class DialogueHandler cannot be applied to given types; sendNpcChat4("I'm sorry, "+c.playerName+", I don't see", "any votes recorded by you. Make sure", "you voted correctly and try", "again. Talk to me when you're done.", c.talkingNpc, "Vote Master"); ^ required: String,String,String,String,int,String,int found: String,String,String,String,int,String reason: actual and formal argument lists differ in length Note: Some input files use unchecked or unsafe operations. Note: Recompile with -Xlint:unchecked for details. 3 errors Compile Finished! Press any key to continue . . .[/code]

item.title: 3 Errors adding vote shop
item.dc:creator: @pure2ownage Pure_
item.description:
@pure2ownage wrote:

You aren’t using the function correctly, ie void a(String s) is the usage but you’re doing a(x, s) - (either an incorrect amount or different types in different places). Try following the tutorial again.

required: String,String,String,String,int,String,int
found: String,String,String,String,int,String
reason: actual and formal argument lists differ in length
